.container
    h1.page-header Timestamp microsvervice
    .exercise
        h3 User stories:
        blockquote 
            ol
                li I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016).
                li If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
                li If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
    .solution.jumbotron
        .container-fluid
            .col-xs-12.col-md-6
                h3 Example usage:
                ul
                    li: a(href="./timestamp/December%2015,%202015", target="_blank")
                        code ./timestamp/December%2015,%202015
                    br
                    li: a(href="./timestamp/1450134000000", target="_blank")
                        code ./timestamp/1450134000000
                    br
                    li: a(href="./timestamp/145013760dsadsadsa0", target="_blank")
                        code ./timestamp/1450137dsadsadsa600

            .col-xs-12.col-md-6
                h3 Example output:
                ul: li
                    code
                        |  { 
                        |      "unix": 1450137600,
                        |      "natural": "December 15, 2015" 
                        |  }

